Odm leader Raila Odinga has given the clearest indication yet that he is ready to work with the One Kenya Alliance. The ODM leader says the party will this week hold a delegates&rsquo; conference in Nyanza the first such meeting planned for all regions in the country to seek delegates approval for the party to engage other political outfits. Odinga says ODM will be ready for talks with Oka and any other political outfit after the final delegates conference to be held in Nairobi.